rcle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"50px\" alignment=\"left\"][/fusion_separator]\r\nAt Reamer Dentistry, Wilmington\'s Cosmetic Dentist, Dr. Daniel and Richard Reamer, artistically create beautiful smiles for the residents of Wilmington, NC.\r\n\r\nA beautiful smile conveys warmth, vitality, and charm, increasing your attractiveness and giving you an edge, socially and professionally. As aesthetic dentists, Dr. Daniel Reamer or Dr. Richard Reamer can transform your smile through modern cosmetic dentistry. Whether you are in need of dental implants, crowns, or any other cosmetic dentistry procedure, you can be confident that <strong>cosmetic dentist in Wilmington, </strong>Drs. Reamer &amp; Reamer have the skills, knowledge, and experience to get the job done.\r\n\r\nYour dentist will discuss your idea of an outstanding smile and assess your oral health, then tailor a treatment plan to meet your goals. You’ll benefit from our dentists’ gentle touch, extensive experience, and training as <strong>cosmetic dentist</strong>. Drs. Reamer &amp; Reamer offer a wide range of procedures for a captivating smile and increased self-confidence. From porcelain veneers to Invisalign® clear braces, we can give you the smile you’ve always wanted.\r\n<h2>Smile Makeovers</h2>\r\n<div id=\"stcpDiv\">\r\n\r\nIf you want a smile that turns heads, you need a complete smile makeover from Reamer Dentistry! A smile makeover is essentially a redesign of your teeth, custom matched to your unique facial appearance and personality. Two or more NC cosmetic dentistry treatments are combined to give you specific smile results that will take your smile from simple to stunning.\r\n\r\nDuring your smile makeover consultation, our dentists will discuss the benefits of our most popular smile makeover procedures including porcelain veneers, <a href=\"/dental-services/dental-crown/\">porcelain crowns</a>, <a href=\"http://www.wilmingtonncdentists.com/dental-services/wilmington-nc-implants/\">porcelain fillings</a>, <a href=\"/dental-services/wilmington-teeth-whitening/\">tooth whitening</a>, gum treatment, <a href=\"/dental-services/wilmington-nc-implants/\">dental implants</a> and <a href=\"http://www.wilmingtonncdentists.com/dental-services/wilmington-nc-dentures/\">dentures</a>.\r\n\r\nContact our office today to schedule your appointment with us. We are happy to discuss your specific dental needs and suggest cosmetic alternatives to a better smile. We look forward to meeting with you!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n[/fusion_text][fusion_separator style_type=\"none\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" sep_color=\"\" top_margin=\"50\" bottom_margin=\"\" border_size=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_circle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"\" alignment=\"center\" /][/fusion_builder_column][/fusion_builder_row][/fusion_builder_container]','Cosmetic Dentistry','','publish','closed','closed','','cosmetic-dentistry','','','2017-06-28 11:05:06','2017-06-28 11:05:06','',31,'http://reamer3.wpengine.com/?page_id=62',0,'page','',0),(63,2,'2017-06-16 12:36:30','2017-06-16 12:36:30','[fusion_builder_container admin_label=\"\" hundred_percent=\"no\" equal_height_columns=\"no\" menu_anchor=\"\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_position=\"center center\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" fade=\"no\" background_parallax=\"none\" enable_mobile=\"no\" parallax_speed=\"0.3\" video_mp4=\"\" video_webm=\"\" video_ogv=\"\" video_url=\"\" video_aspect_ratio=\"16:9\" video_loop=\"yes\" video_mute=\"yes\" video_preview_image=\"\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"solid\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" padding_top=\"0px\" padding_right=\"\" padding_bottom=\"\" padding_left=\"0px\"][fusion_builder_row][fusion_builder_column type=\"1_1\" layout=\"3_4\" spacing=\"\" center_content=\"no\" hover_type=\"none\" link=\"\" min_height=\"\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_position=\"left top\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" border_size=\"0\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"solid\" border_position=\"all\" padding=\"\" dimension_margin=\"\" animation_type=\"\" animation_direction=\"left\" animation_speed=\"0.3\" animation_offset=\"\" last=\"no\"][fusion_text]<h1>Dental Bridges in Wilmington</h1>\r\n[fusion_separator style_type=\"single solid\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" sep_color=\"#3b5a70\" top_margin=\"20\" bottom_margin=\"20\" border_size=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_circle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"50px\" alignment=\"left\"][/fusion_separator]\r\nWhen a patient is missing one or multiple teeth, one option for replacement are dental bridges (or bridge work). Dental bridges can replace one or multiple teeth and can be made of many different materials dependent on location, esthetic needs and functional needs.\r\n<p class=\"faq\">Dental Bridges work can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Restore your smile</li>\r\n 	<li>Restore your ability to properly chew and speak</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintain the shape of your face</li>\r\n 	<li>Distribute the forces in your bite properly by replacing missing teeth</li>\r\n 	<li>Prevent remaining teeth from drifting out of position</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>What are Dental Bridges?</h2>\r\nDental bridges literally “bridge the gap” between one or more missing teeth. A dental bridge consists of:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>two crowns</strong>, one for each of the teeth on either side of the gap,</li>\r\n 	<li>and a <strong>false tooth/teeth</strong> in-between your two natural teeth or dental implants.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThese false teeth are made from <strong>porcelain </strong>and are supported by your natural teeth (or implants).\r\n<h2>The Porcelain Bridge Procedure</h2>\r\nThe dentist will begin your dental bridge work by filing down the adjacent teeth to accommodate the crowns. Then, the dentist will take impressions of the teeth, which will be used to create the porcelain crowns.\r\n\r\nOnce the crowns are finished (crowns are made from all-ceramic materials), the false tooth (teeth) will be bonded to them. When the <strong>porcelain bridge is ready</strong>, a return visit to the dentist will be necessary to place it on the teeth. During your final visit, the dentist securely cements the crowns over the surrounding teeth to complete your smile with the dental bridge. With proper care, dental bridges will last five to seven years and, in some cases, longer.[/fusion_text][fusion_separator style_type=\"none\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" sep_color=\"\" top_margin=\"50\" bottom_margin=\"\" border_size=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_circle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"\" alignment=\"center\" /][/fusion_builder_column][/fusion_builder_row][/fusion_builder_container]','Dental Bridges','','publish','closed','closed','','dental-bridges','','','2017-07-05 20:25:04','2017-07-05 20:25:04','',31,'http://reamer3.wpengine.com/?page_id=63',0,'page','',0),(64,2,'2017-06-16 12:39:37','2017-06-16 12:39:37','[fusion_builder_container admin_label=\"\" hundred_percent=\"no\" equal_height_columns=\"no\" menu_anchor=\"\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_position=\"center center\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" fade=\"no\" background_parallax=\"none\" enable_mobile=\"no\" parallax_speed=\"0.3\" video_mp4=\"\" video_webm=\"\" video_ogv=\"\" video_url=\"\" video_aspect_ratio=\"16:9\" video_loop=\"yes\" video_mute=\"yes\" video_preview_image=\"\" border_size=\"\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"solid\" margin_top=\"\" margin_bottom=\"\" padding_top=\"0px\" padding_right=\"\" padding_bottom=\"\" padding_left=\"0px\"][fusion_builder_row][fusion_builder_column type=\"1_1\" layout=\"3_4\" spacing=\"\" center_content=\"no\" hover_type=\"none\" link=\"\" min_height=\"\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_position=\"left top\" background_repeat=\"no-repeat\" border_size=\"0\" border_color=\"\" border_style=\"solid\" border_position=\"all\" padding=\"\" dimension_margin=\"\" animation_type=\"\" animation_direction=\"left\" animation_speed=\"0.3\" animation_offset=\"\" last=\"no\"][fusion_text]\r\n<h1>Dental Crowns</h1>\r\n[fusion_separator style_type=\"single solid\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" sep_color=\"#3b5a70\" top_margin=\"20\" bottom_margin=\"20\" border_size=\"\" icon=\"\" icon_circle=\"\" icon_circle_color=\"\" width=\"50px\" alignment=\"left\"][/fusion_separator]\r\n<p class=\"faq\">Dental crowns are tooth-shaped “caps” that are placed over teeth – covering teeth to restore their shape and size, strength and/or to improve their appearance.</p>\r\n<p class=\"faq\">A dental crown may be needed in the following situations:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>To protect a weak tooth (for instance, from decay) from breaking or to hold together parts of a cracked tooth</li>\r\n 	<li>To restore an already broken tooth or a tooth that has been severely worn down</li>\r\n 	<li>To cover and support a tooth with a large filling when there isn’t a lot of tooth left</li>\r\n 	<li>To hold a dental bridge in place</li>\r\n 	<li>To cover misshapened or severely discolored teeth</li>\r\n 	<li>To cover a dental implant</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[/fusion_text][/fusion_builder_column][fusion_builder_column type=\"1_1\" layout=\"1_1\" spacing=\"\" center_content=\"no\" hover_type=\"none\" link=\"\" min_height=\"\" hide_on_mobile=\"small-visibility,medium-visibility,large-visibility\" class=\"\" id=\"\" background_color=\"\" background_image=\"\" background_po